headline: AI pioneer Fei-Fei Li's World Labs raises $1 billion in funding
summary: Prominent computer scientist Fei-Fei Li's World Labs raised $1 billion in a funding round as the ‌startup accelerates its efforts to advance "spatial intelligence," it said ‌on Wednesday.  The startup said the investors included semiconductor companies AMD, Nvidia, software firm ​Autodesk, Emerson Collective, Fidelity Management & Research Company and Sea, among others.  Separately, Autodesk said it invested $200 million in World Labs and will serve as an adviser to the startup.
